body:
I have a rectangle and I want to get the remaining bounding rectangle after subtracting other rectangles from it. However, after passing `SKClipOperation.Difference` to the `ClipRect` method, the clip bounds always remain unchanged.

In this example, rect2 of height 50 is the bottom half of rect1 (height 100). I create a surface using the details of rect1:

    SKRect rect1 = new SKRect(10, 10, 110, 110);
    SKRect rect2 = new SKRect(10, 60, 110, 110);

    SKImageInfo info = new SKImageInfo((int)rect1.Width, (int)rect1.Height);

    using (SKSurface surface = SKSurface.Create(info)) {
        surface.Canvas.Translate(-rect1.Left, -rect1.Top);

Then I attempt to subtract rect2 from the clip region, but the clip bounds remain unchanged. I've also tried rectangular `SKPath` objects and used them with `ClipPath`, but got the same result. Is there something I'm missing?

        surface.Canvas.ClipRect(rect2, SKClipOperation.Difference);

This works however. Intersecting with rect2 reduces the clip bounds to a height of 50:

        surface.Canvas.ClipRect(rect2, SKClipOperation.Intersect);
    }
